9.How do you delete 30 days old files?
Ans: find /path/to/directory -type f -mtime +30 -delete

/path/to/directory â†’ Replace with the folder you want to clean up.

-type f â†’ Targets files only.

-mtime +30 â†’ Matches files modified more than 30 days ago.

-delete â†’ Deletes the matching files.


10.How do find all log files that are modified in the last 7 days?
Ans: find /path/to/directory -type f -name *.log -mtime -7

/path/to/search â†’ Directory where you want to search (e.g., /var/log).

-type f â†’ Looks for files only.

-name "*.log" â†’ Matches files with .log extension.

-mtime -7 â†’ Modified within the last 7 days

